    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "320e075b_980ffe6f",
        "filename": "resultdb/recorder/chromium/swarming.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-05T01:41:51Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hm, come to think of it this bit is a little strange because we don\u0027t expect invocations from swarming tasks /not/ to be finalized. In particular, if we get a task that already has its invocation (possibly deduped) uploaded, then we don\u0027t need to return the TestResults for the client to call BatchCreateTestResults (which would only have effect on a non-finalized invocation anyway).\n\nSo we can either have DeriveInvocation return nil TestResults in this case, which means clients shouldn\u0027t expect to be able to inspect any TestResults from a DeriveInvocation response, or we can fetch the associated TestResults and return them, which seems wasteful here because it\u0027ll be an extra RPC to Spanner without having any guaranteed use later, but doesn\u0027t have potentially surprising behavior. Thoughts? (I\u0027ve gone with the first alternative for now but am happy to change it)",
      "parentUuid": "94beace0_20b0bbcc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "92792b0d9c14694c98a7e249e77af9f51f2989fa",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "23c4694a_c8349918",
        "filename": "resultdb/recorder/chromium/swarming.go",
        "patchSetId": 9
      },
      "lineNbr": 77,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-05T04:46:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think these are great points!\n\n1) yes, it would require read test results right here, which essentially duplication of ListTestResults RPC. Looks like we need to change DeriveInvocation RPC to return Invocation message, and ditch DeriveInvocationResponse entirely. So let\u0027s return Invocation in this func? Sorry, this is exactly what you had before.\n\n2) yes, it is an exception to have a swarming-derived non-finalized task. In such case, it is better to fail fast by returning an INTERNAL error (because it would indicate that something went wrong in our code)",
      "parentUuid": "320e075b_980ffe6f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 77,
        "startChar": 15,
        "endLine": 77,
        "endChar": 48
      },
